  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "9. We gat our bread with … peril—that is, those of us left in the city after its capture by the Chaldeans.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "because of … sword of … wilderness—because of the liability to attack by the robber Arabs of the wilderness, through which the Jews had to pass to get \"bread\" from Egypt (compare La 5:6).",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
